text:
{'text': 'Presentation of the food was great but taste was average. Felt that the burger was really quite meh. Popeye chicken tastes better. The fries was really ordinary as well.

Truffle pasta was quite delicious. Apple crumble is yummy too

Went around 140 pm on a Sunday noon and the dining experience was totally ruined by a table of around 8-10 rowdy kids accompanied by a couple who seriously lack dining etiquette.
Very rowdy and noisy with the boys shouting at the top of their voices while playing their games on the phone.

Take it home or to outdoor dining if you really have to KB since the restaurant is not closed off for your private dining. Shame on the adults who did nothing and have to be asked by the server to be considerate

Service of the staff is great. Cheerful and attentive', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJCwSH5AUZ2jER0ARBxL1oD2k/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VObkQ2OExpLXZlZ1RnEAE
text:
{'text': "Food: 4.5/10
I ordered their Assembly burger which they put a 'Star' there means is a signature dish? To me, personally I think the patty doesnt suit the bun at all, steak is harder to chew. I bite both burger and steak together but after 1 min, im still chewing the steak and the bun is already devoured... I would prefer their patty beef instead of steak next time.
Fries was pretty normal, price also dont seems to match the burger.

I will be back for other dish and re-rate this cafe. Sorryz.

I ordered only 1 main dish and thats all, will change the rating once i tried another dish.
Service: service was great. Crew are nice.", 'languageCode': 'en'}

text: {'text': 'A mildly overpriced brunch cafe, with okay food and coffee. Decent locations and okay service.\n\nRandom gripe about the "Assembly Burger": Paid 30$ for a weird steak burger. More emphasis on the "steak" than the burger - because it\'s two pieces of steak that you need to eat with a knife and fork, put on a bun. (So no eating it with your hands like an actual burger)', 'languageCode': 'en'}
